content.description:
Climb Left El Myles, clip a lone bolt, then hook into Bats in the Bellfree. Top may still need additional scrubbing. Pretty great movement on both sections!

If anyone else has done this before me, don't let me steal your thunder and let me know!
content.protection: Pads and 3 draws. Rest are fixed.
content.location: Located in the back of Sean's Cave

content.description: Start sitting on the obvious tufas at the back of the cave. Pinch your way out tufas just to the left of the big hole. Make powerful moves up to an obvious finish jug at 12 ft. Wild features.
content.location: Located at the very back of Sean's cave.

content.description: Start deep in the cave and move through the pockets on the left.  After exiting the cave, transition to face climbing through 3 more bolts on the face to the set of anchors on the left.
content.protection: 6 bolts to chain Anchors.   Shares anchors with A Man’s Undoing.
content.location: Starts in the cave. Shares the same 4-bolt start with Alotta.

content.description: Start deep in the cave and move through the pockets on the left.  Exit cave and mantle to the shelf above the cave.  Continue climbing straight up through one more bolt to obvious chains directly above the cave.
content.location: Starts in the cave.  Shares the same 4-bolt start with Bat’s in the Bellfree.

content.description: Start on the grey streak down low and move through the bulges up high. Gaston to underclings.
content.protection: 4 bolts to chain Anchors.  Shares anchors with Bat’s in the Bellfree.
content.location: This is the route on the west facing wall, left of the cave.
